The Forest of Confusion -- Quarantine Ledger Contamination Advisory

The Quarantine Ledger classifies the Forest of Confusion as a
Crystal Contamination Source, Tier Three. The forest lies north
of Kiess in territory we have no cause to patrol. But contaminated
material does not respect jurisdictional boundaries, and the Ledger's
Hazard Scribes track threats by what they produce, not where they sit.

The core problem: the Spirebound Conclave embedded crystal matrices
in the forest's root systems and abandoned them without filing a
single decommission record. This is unattested hazardous
installation -- active material with no manifest, no chain of
custody, and no responsible authority. Under the Dual-Attestation
Protocol, such material cannot be cleared at any classification level.

The confusion mists were once a deliberate quarantine created by
druids to contain the contamination. That containment has failed.
The druidic order died demographically, and without maintenance the
mists lost their calibrated purpose -- an unattested hazard
operating without oversight, diffusing outward without constraint.

Our Harbor Wardens recognize the pattern. A quarantine requires a
living authority maintaining it. When the authority dies, the
quarantine becomes the hazard. This is why the Quarantine Ledger is
staffed by apprentice-chains, never single practitioners. A system
that dies with its keeper was never a system.

If crystal-contaminated artifacts reach our port -- carried by Kiess
traders who may not know their provenance -- the Quarantine Ledger
flags them on resonance signature alone. Our Hazard Scribes maintain
a reference catalog of Conclave crystal profiles inherited from
Khar'Daan's containment archives. We can identify what the interior
authorities cannot.

The Broken Ones degraded by crystal exposure concern us as evidence
of contamination intensity. Mafdet heals without prejudice and never
asks where you came from. But if you arrive bearing crystal resonance,
the Quarantine Ledger documents the exposure and the Harbor Wardens
direct you to the healing houses first. Compassion and attestation
are not opposed.

The Neogi slavers exploiting the fog are classified Hostile
Commerce, Unattested Labor. Slave-trade goods carry no legitimate
provenance. The Shrine of the First Claw does not recognize commerce
built on stolen guardian-names.

Three institutions failed here -- the Conclave created, the druids
contained, Kiess manages the symptoms. Mafdet will not inherit the
consequences quietly.

